#: src/tools/browser.md
msgid "**URL scheme policy.** `browser_open` accepts both `http://` and `https://` URLs (matching `web_fetch`, `http_request`, and the `browser` tool, which already accept plaintext HTTP). The local/private-host block and the `allowed_domains` allowlist apply to `http://` exactly as they do to `https://`. Because `allowed_domains` defaults to `[\"*\"]`, the shipped default permits opening **any public host over plaintext HTTP**. To reduce plaintext-HTTP exposure, replace the wildcard allowlist with the specific public hosts you trust. Note this **does not enforce HTTPS** for those hosts: the allowlist gates origins, not schemes; HTTPS-only behavior for an allowed host requires that host to redirect/reject plaintext HTTP itself (HSTS, server-side 308), or a future scheme-aware browser policy."
msgstr "**URL 方案策略。** `browser_open` 同时接受 `http://` 和 `https://` URL（与 `web_fetch`、`http_request` 以及 `browser` 工具一致，它们已经接受明文 HTTP）。本地/私有主机阻止规则和 `allowed_domains` 白名单对 `http://` 的适用方式与 `https://` 完全相同。由于 `allowed_domains` 默认是 `[\"*\"]`，因此随附的默认配置允许通过明文 HTTP 打开**任何公共主机**。为减少明文 HTTP 暴露，请用你信任的具体公共主机替换通配白名单。注意，这**不会强制 HTTPS** 适用于这些主机：白名单限制的是来源，而不是协议；对允许主机的仅 HTTPS 行为，需要该主机自身重定向/拒绝明文 HTTP（HSTS、服务端 308），或采用未来支持按协议感知的浏览器策略。"

