#: src/developing/plugin-protocol.md
msgid "Be aware of the gap between declared and enforced: in the component host today `config_read` and `http_client` have behavioral effect. `runtime.rs` passes a tool plugin's resolved config section into `execute` only when the manifest grants `config_read`, and strips any caller-supplied `__config` so the section cannot be spoofed; a channel plugin receives the same section through its `configure` export under the same rule. `http_client` attaches an outbound `wasi:http` context to the plugin's store and links the `wasi:http` interface, so a granted plugin can make HTTP requests and one without the permission has no network surface at all. The remaining variants (`file_read`, `file_write`, `memory_read`, `memory_write`) are accepted by the manifest schema but are not yet wired to a host import: declaring them grants nothing on its own. They reserve the names for the host functions that will gate them (see Host imports below)."
msgstr "请注意声明与实际强制执行之间的差距：在当前的 component host 中，`config_read` 和 `http_client` 具有行为上的效果。`runtime.rs` 仅在 manifest 授予 `config_read` 时，才会将工具插件已解析的 config section 传入 `execute`，并且会剥离任何调用方提供的 `__config`，因此该 section 不可能被伪造；通道插件则会在相同规则下，通过其 `configure` 导出接收相同的 section。`http_client` 会向插件的 store 附加一个出站 `wasi:http` 上下文，并链接 `wasi:http` 接口，因此被授予权限的插件可以发起 HTTP 请求，而没有该权限的插件则完全没有网络面。其余变体（`file_read`、`file_write`、`memory_read`、`memory_write`）已被 manifest schema 接受，但尚未接入 host import：仅仅声明它们本身不会授予任何权限。它们只是为将来用于限制它们的 host 函数预留了名称（见下方 Host imports）。"

