#: src/contributing/pr-review-protocol.md
msgid "Missing required substance is a review finding. If the content is present but the heading or placement needs mechanical cleanup, and a maintainer can safely repair it, fix or propose the exact cleanup instead of making the author do metadata work. When acting through an assistant, show the exact PR-body or metadata diff and get human reviewer approval before mutating GitHub. If the missing section is substantive, unsupported, or changes reviewer confidence, do not approve until it is filled."
