msgid "Optional methods are advertised through `flags channel-capabilities` and `flags memory-capabilities`. Because flags are a bitmask, new optional methods can be added to a `vN/` package without a breaking change, paired with a new `@since` function. Removing or renaming a flag, function, field, or variant case is breaking and requires a new `vN+1/` directory."
