#: src/architecture/memory-payload-lifecycle.md
msgid "Tool-call observability needs extra care because the sinks do not share one payload contract. Current typed tool-call observer events can carry full arguments and credential-scrubbed full result output, and OTel forwards those values into span attributes. Do not describe that path as \"summaries\" unless the code actually bounds or summarizes it. New telemetry should prefer bounded identifiers, counts, durations, success flags, and operator-useful summaries. Put raw content in logs or observer events only when the feature explicitly requires it and the privacy boundary is documented."
msgstr "工具调用可观测性需要额外谨慎，因为各个接收端并不共享同一种载荷契约。当前带类型的工具调用观察器事件可以携带完整参数以及经过凭据清理的完整结果输出，而 OTel 会将这些值转发到 span 属性中。除非代码实际对其进行了边界限制或摘要处理，否则不要将这一路径描述为“摘要”。新的遥测应优先使用受限标识符、计数、持续时间、成功标志以及对操作员有用的摘要。只有在该功能明确要求且已记录隐私边界时，才将原始内容放入日志或观察器事件中。"

#: src/architecture/memory-payload-lifecycle.md
msgid "Tool-call pairing matters more than byte savings. A history change must not leave a provider request with a dangling `tool_use` without the matching `tool_result`, or the reverse."
msgstr "工具调用配对比节省字节更重要。历史更改绝不能让提供方请求中留下没有匹配 `tool_result` 的悬空 `tool_use`，反之亦然。"

