msgstr "没有密钥就无法验证：在该模式下请勿公开暴露此端点。"

#: src/architecture/decisions/ADR-004-tool-shared-state-ownership.md
msgid "Without a shared contract, new tools risk introducing duplicate state, data leaks between clients, stale state after reloads, or blocking startup validation in the wrong lifecycle phase."
msgstr "如果没有共享契约，新工具可能会引入重复状态、客户端之间的数据泄漏、重载后的陈旧状态，或者在错误的生命周期阶段阻塞启动验证。"

#: src/foundations/fnd-002-documentation-standards.md
msgid "Without an answer to that question, documentation accumulates as a pile of pages that are all slightly different shapes of the same vague category: \"stuff about the project.\" Setup guides live next to architecture decisions. User-facing how-tos sit alongside internal coding standards. Thirty language translations of the README compete for space with the single security policy document. Nobody can find anything, everything goes stale at a different rate, and every PR that touches documentation becomes a negotiation about which pages need updating."
msgstr "如果没有对这一问题的解答，文档就会堆积成一大堆页面，它们都属于同一个模糊类别的不同变体：“关于项目的资料”。设置指南与架构决策并列，面向用户的使用指南与内部编码规范并存。README 的三十种语言翻译与安全策略文档争夺空间。没有人能找到任何东西，所有内容以不同的速度过时，每一个涉及文档的 PR 都变成了一场关于哪些页面需要更新的谈判。"

#: src/architecture/decisions/ADR-002-trait-driven-extensibility.md
msgid "Without explicit contracts, every integration would pressure the runtime loop to grow special cases. That would make new integrations faster at first and harder to maintain later: provider routing would leak into channels, tool policy would leak into providers, channel authentication would leak into the agent loop, and memory or logging behavior would be copied across unrelated crates."
msgstr "如果没有明确的契约，每个集成都会迫使运行时循环不断增加特殊分支。这会让新的集成一开始更快，但日后更难维护：provider 路由会泄漏到 channels，tool policy 会泄漏到 providers，channel authentication 会泄漏到 agent loop，而 memory 或 logging 行为会被复制到彼此无关的 crates 中。"

